{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"3720C","heading":"Debt Collection Improvement Account","label":"3720C Debt Collection Improvement Account","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/stIII/ch37/schII","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3720C","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","References in TextThe Congressional Budget Act of 1974, referred to in subsec. (d), is titles I through IX of , , . Title V of the Act, known as the Federal Credit Reform Act of 1990, is classified generally to subchapter III (§ 661 et seq.) of chapter 17A of Title 2, The Congress. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under and Tables.Pub. L. 93–34488 Stat. 297section 621 of Title 2July 12, 1974"],"amendments":["References in TextThe Congressional Budget Act of 1974, referred to in subsec. (d), is titles I through IX of , , . Title V of the Act, known as the Federal Credit Reform Act of 1990, is classified generally to subchapter III (§ 661 et seq.) of chapter 17A of Title 2, The Congress. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under and Tables.Pub. L. 93–34488 Stat. 297section 621 of Title 2July 12, 1974"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":null,"label":"a","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3720C%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3720C%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"There is hereby established in the Treasury a special fund to be known as the “Debt Collection Improvement Account” (hereinafter in this section referred to as the “Account”).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3720C%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Account shall be maintained and managed by the Secretary of the Treasury, who shall ensure that agency programs are credited with amounts transferred under subsection (b)(1).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":null,"label":"b","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3720C%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3720C%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Not later than 30 days after the end of a fiscal year, an agency may transfer to the Account the amount described in paragraph (3), as adjusted under paragraph (4).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3720C%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/b/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3720C%2Fb%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"salary, administrative, and tax refund offsets;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/b/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3720C%2Fb%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Department of Justice;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/b/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3720C%2Fb%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"private collection agencies;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/b/2/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3720C%2Fb%2F2%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"sales of delinquent loans; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"E","heading":null,"label":"E","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/b/2/E","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3720C%2Fb%2F2%2FE","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"contracts to locate or recover assets.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3720C%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/b/3/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/b/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3720C%2Fb%2F3%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"5 percent of the amount of delinquent nontax debt collected by the agency in the previous fiscal year, or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/b/3/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/b/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3720C%2Fb%2F3%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"5 percent of the average annual amount of delinquent nontax debt collected by the agency in the previous 4 fiscal years.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/b/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3720C%2Fb%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/b/4/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/b/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3720C%2Fb%2F4%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The number of days between the date a claim or debt became delinquent and the date which an agency referred the debt or claim to the Secretary of the Treasury or obtained an exemption from this referral under .section 3711(g)(2) of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/b/4/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/b/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3720C%2Fb%2F4%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The ratio of delinquent debts or claims to total receivables for a given program, and the change in this ratio over a period of time.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":null,"label":"c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3720C%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3720C%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary of the Treasury may make payments from the Account solely to reimburse agencies for qualified expenses. For agencies with franchise funds, such payments may be credited to subaccounts designated for debt collection.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3720C%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/c/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3720C%2Fc%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"account servicing (including cross-servicing under ),section 3711(g) of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/c/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3720C%2Fc%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"automatic data processing equipment acquisitions,","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/c/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3720C%2Fc%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"delinquent debt collection,","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/c/2/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3720C%2Fc%2F2%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"measures to minimize delinquent debt,","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"E","heading":null,"label":"E","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/c/2/E","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3720C%2Fc%2F2%2FE","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"sales of delinquent debt,","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"F","heading":null,"label":"F","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/c/2/F","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3720C%2Fc%2F2%2FF","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"asset disposition, and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"G","heading":null,"label":"G","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/c/2/G","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3720C%2Fc%2F2%2FG","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"training of personnel involved in credit and debt management.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/c/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3720C%2Fc%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/c/3/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/c/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3720C%2Fc%2F3%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Amounts transferred to the Account shall be available to the Secretary of the Treasury for purposes of this section to the extent and in amounts provided in advance in appropriations Acts.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/c/3/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/c/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3720C%2Fc%2F3%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"As soon as practicable after the end of the third fiscal year after which amounts transferred are first available pursuant to this section, and every 3 years thereafter, any uncommitted balance in the Account shall be transferred to the general fund of the Treasury as miscellaneous receipts.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":null,"label":"d","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3720C%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"For direct loans and loan guarantee programs subject to title V of the Congressional Budget Act of 1974, amounts credited in accordance with subsection (c) shall be considered administrative costs.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"e","heading":null,"label":"e","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C/e","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3720C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3720C%2Fe","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary of the Treasury shall prescribe such rules, regulations, and procedures as the Secretary considers necessary or appropriate to carry out the purposes of this section.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}
